title: S. Jersey Girls: Morocco powers Holy Cross past Bordentown
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Lily Garrett netted the winner in overtime to give Palmyra the 2-1 edge at Florence. Lily Beck tied it for the visitors. Haley Jusino scored for Florence.
Caroline Rockhill scored twice in Rancocas Valley's 4-2 win at No. 9 Moorestown. Kayla Flanders and Mekenzie Montgomery each added a goal. Lexi Pestritto and Iasia Goeloe each had a pair of assists. Theresa Adu-Attobrah made 10 saves. 
Hailey Russell scored four goals - increasing the freshman's total to 27 this season - in Riverside's 6-0 shutout of visiting Willingboro. 
JennaRose Scimone scored and assisted on a pair of goals as Burlington Township rolled over Pennsauken at home, 5-0. Brittany Bachich, Nicole Binkley, Gabriella Senni, and Francesca Stevens also scored. Hailey Bachich and Kate Field each had an assist. 
Olympic. Steph Tollefson scored six minutes into overtime to send Seneca over host Bishop Eustace, 3-2. Dani LeSaint and Emily Meale also scored. 
Tziarra King scored twice to lift Winslow Township over host Paul VI, 2-1. Jalissa Pitts had the assist. Brianna Breen registered seven saves. 
Amirah Ali and Jaylyn Thompson each netted a pair of goals in top-ranked Eastern's 5-1 win at No. 5 Washington Township. Ali also had an assist. Rachel Wood scored and dished out an assist. 
Sarina Jones scored twice for Timber Creek in a 4-0 shutout at Camden Catholic. Skye Hunt registered three saves to earn the win. 
Cape-Atlantic. Tori Rolls and Natale Stinson both scored to give Ocean City the 2-1 edge at Oakcrest. Jenna Steelman scored for the hosts. Brooke Segich made six saves to earn the win. Field Hockey Gab Bodine scored twice in Cherokee's 5-0 win at Cherry Hill West in an Olympic Conference matchup.
Brooke Yarsinsky scored and added an assist. Christina Orio and Joelle Wash each added a goal. 
Burlington County. Serefina Kennedy scored in overtime to give Cinnaminson a 1-0 shutout at Northern Burlington. Lauren Friedrich made four saves. 
Cape-Atlantic. Jenna Herlihy scored twice and had an assist in Middle Township's 5-0 win at Millville. Skylar Gentilini, Honna Hippen, and Abby Thompson also scored. 
Selena Carter's goal was the difference in Pennsauken's 1-0 win over visiting Cherry Hill East. Indigo Pascall had the assist. Tennis Katie Pileggi won at second singles, 7-5, 6-4, to aid host Haddonfield in a 3-2 nonleague win over Moorestown.
In first doubles, Lizzy Benedict and Sarah Smith won their match, 6-2, 6-4. 
In another nonleague match, Stephanie Yanosov knocked off her opponent at first singles, 6-0, 6-0, as Cherry Hill East defeated visiting Cherokee, 4-1. Sarah Jang and Rebekah Colacot won at second doubles, 6-0, 6-3. 
Olympic. Taryn Atmore outlasted her opponent at third singles, 4-6, 8-6, 10-8, to help Seneca beat host Eastern, 3-2. Tori Felt and Yvette Kurian won their first-doubles contest, 6-0, 6-4.
